Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Cut @broccoli{1%unit} into bite-size pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}; set aside.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @Fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes}. (For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast potatoes on top rack and broccoli on middle rack.)

After 10 minutes, carefully toss broccoli on empty side of baking sheet with a drizzle of cooking oil, salt, and pepper and continue to roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, lemon zest, and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} in a large #zip-close bag{}. Season with @salt{1%tsp} and @pepper{}.

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork if preferred.

Place @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} in a #medium bowl{}; add beef and turn to coat.

Place coated beef in zip-close bag with panko mixture and seal to close. Shake until beef is evenly coated.

> You may need to move beef around in bag, pressing with your hands, to spread out panko and make it stick.

Heat a 1⁄4-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a large, #heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to pan, add beef.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cook until panko is golden and beef is cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> For thicker pork chops, cook 1-2 minutes more.

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

> Cook chicken as instructed or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Divide beef, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Serve with lemon wedges on the side and creamy mustard sauce for dipping or drizzling.